<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,725,1038]" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">Holotype male seen; greasy and the colour pattern completely obscured, mid legs missing, posterior margin of both wings damaged.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="512" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,725,1038]" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,797,822]" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
General colour pale grey dusted; ocellar triangle embossed with apex truncate (
<figureCitation box="[1236,1318,797,822]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 40" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,212,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[179,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 40. Sternite 5; cercal plate and surstyli in dorsal view; epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli in lateral view; aedeagus in lateral view: 25 – 28. Limnophora gilvifrons (Emden). 29 – 32. Limnophora kinangopana Emden. 33 – 36. Limnophora latilamellata Malloch. 37 – 40. Limnophora longiseta Emden." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242399/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1290,1318,798,822]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.636" pageId="11" pageNumber="512" unit="in" value="34.0">34</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Emden" pageId="11" pageNumber="512" refString="Emden, F. I. van. (1951) Muscidae: C - Scatophaginae, Anthomyiinae, Lispinae, Fanniinae and Phaoniinae. In: Ruwenzori Expedition 1934 - 35, vol. 2, British Museum (Natural History), London, 325 - 710." type="book chapter" year="1951">Emden 1951</bibRefCitation>
: 448) and reaching lunule; postsutural dorscentrals 3; mid femur with two preapical setae; mid tibia with 2 posterior setae; sternite 5 (
<figureCitation box="[447,528,869,894]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 40" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,212,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[179,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 40. Sternite 5; cercal plate and surstyli in dorsal view; epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli in lateral view; aedeagus in lateral view: 25 – 28. Limnophora gilvifrons (Emden). 29 – 32. Limnophora kinangopana Emden. 33 – 36. Limnophora latilamellata Malloch. 37 – 40. Limnophora longiseta Emden." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242399/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,725,1038]" box="[199,1190,905,930]" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">
Terminalia. Cercal plate and surstylus as in 
<figureCitation box="[688,817,905,930]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 40" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,212,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[179,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 40. Sternite 5; cercal plate and surstyli in dorsal view; epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli in lateral view; aedeagus in lateral view: 25 – 28. Limnophora gilvifrons (Emden). 29 – 32. Limnophora kinangopana Emden. 33 – 36. Limnophora latilamellata Malloch. 37 – 40. Limnophora longiseta Emden." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242399/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">Figs 26–27</figureCitation>
. Aedeagal complex as in 
<figureCitation box="[1103,1185,905,930]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 40" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,212,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[179,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 40. Sternite 5; cercal plate and surstyli in dorsal view; epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli in lateral view; aedeagus in lateral view: 25 – 28. Limnophora gilvifrons (Emden). 29 – 32. Limnophora kinangopana Emden. 33 – 36. Limnophora latilamellata Malloch. 37 – 40. Limnophora longiseta Emden." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242399/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,725,1038]" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1424565241" collectionCode="BMNH" country="South Africa" location="Easily" pageId="11" pageNumber="512" specimenCount="2" stateProvince="A" typeStatus="paratype">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,941,966]" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">Notes.</emphasis>
Described originally in 
<taxonomicName box="[548,662,941,965]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Spilogona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[548,662,941,965]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">Spilogona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. One 
<typeStatus box="[730,827,942,966]" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">paratype</typeStatus>
female is in better condition than the 
<typeStatus box="[1256,1357,941,966]" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">holotype</typeStatus>
, and is pale grey dusted as in the description. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EC4C72F467FF8856F2FD9527CBFBDA:8E9AABBFF467FF88543EFC2E2796FC3D" box="[603,673,977,1002]" country="South Africa" name="Easily" pageId="11" pageNumber="512" stateProvince="A">Easily</location>
recognized by the very characteristic ocellar triangle. 
<collectingRegion box="[1308,1328,978,1002]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">A</collectingRegion>
series of males and females from 
<collectingCountry box="[426,570,1013,1038]" name="South Africa" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">South Africa</collectingCountry>
is in the 
<collectionCode box="[673,761,1014,1037]" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">BMNH</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
